column2: sequences

column1:
'Number of sequences': where sequences are counted the count
should be conducted after quality control UMI processing and
replicate/error cloud removal.

Question for review - should this be the number of distinct
sequences  or a molecule count?

'Reference genes and alleles' - this is the set of genes and
alleles provided to the inference tool.

column2: description

Identifier of the allele (either IMGT, or the name assigned
by the submitter to an inferred gene)
Overall number of sequences assigned to this allele

For inferred alleles, the closest reference gene and allele,
as inferred by the tool

For inferred alleles, the closest reference gene and allele
that is in the subject's inferred genotype, as inferred by
the tool

For inferred alleles, the number of nucleotides that differ
between this sequence and the closest reference gene and
allele

List of nucleotide substitutions (e.g. G112A) between this
sequence and the closest reference gene and allele

For inferred alleles, the number of amino acids that differ
between this sequence and the closest reference gene and
allele

List of amino acid substitutions (e.g. A96N) between this
sequence and the closest reference gene and allele. Please
use IMGT numbering for V-genes, and number from start of
coding sequence for D- or J- genes.

The proportion of unmutated sequences in the dataset
represented by this sequence.

The number of records in the sequence dataset exactly
matching this unmutated sequence

The number of molecules (identified by Unique Molecular
Identifiers) exactly matching this unmutated sequence (if
UMIs were used)

The percentage at which this allele was observed in the
sequence dataset, compared to other alleles

Number of D allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences)
found associated with an inferred V sequence

Number of J allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences)
found associated with an inferred V sequence

Number of unique CDR3s found associated with an inferred V
sequence

Locus (or loci) from which haplotyping was inferred (e.g.
IGHJ6)

Ratio (expressed as two percentages) with which the two
inferred haplotypes were found (e.g. 60:40)
The consensus sequence provided by the inference tool
